Buddies was inspired by the RuneLite GIMP Tracker plugin's product shape.

The curated coordinate-to-place resolver was developed during Trevor Campbell's
location-display experiments in a locally modified GIMP Tracker checkout. It is
not part of upstream GIMP Tracker, and that experiment was the progenitor of
Buddies. The resolver file retains applicable BSD 2-Clause source attribution.

The group model, map rendering, ping overlay, notes, task manager, HTTP
fallback, and GIMP panel code were intentionally not copied.
